### Problem Summary

I am unable to use `page` as a parameter name to my `OnGet()` method.

### Details

I'm trying to add paging to my */Index* page.

So I coded things like:

**Page**

    @page "{page?}

**Code**

    public async Task<IActionResult> OnGetAsync(string page)
    {
        // ...
    }
    
But when `OnGetAsync()` is called with the URL *https://www.domain.com/page=5*, the `page` parameter contains "/Index". It contains the name of the current page instead of the query argument.

If I change the name of my query argument to just `p`, then it works just fine.

### Solution
I can't tell if this is some intended feature. But `page` would actually be a pretty common query argument name to use. I don't see any advantage to what it's doing, but either way I should be able to use a parameter with the name I choose.

### Additional context

This is an ASP.NET Core 3.1 Razor Pages project. Visual Studio version 16.7.2.

I have the following middleware which allows me to change the content after the pipeline has executed:

```
public async Task InvokeAsync(HttpContext httpContext) {
    // Store the "pre-modified" response stream.
    var originBody = httpContext.Response.Body;

    // Set the response body to our stream so we can read after the chain of middleware has been called.
    using var body = new MemoryStream();
    httpContext.Response.Body = body;

    try {
        await _next(httpContext);
    } finally {
        httpContext.Response.Body = originBody;
    }

    var content = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(body.ToArray());

    // Replace content here

    // Write the content to the response stream.
    await httpContext.Response.WriteAsync(content);
}
```

I need this placed after `UseRequestLocalization` which itself must be placed after `UseRouting`. However `UseStatusCodePagesWithReExecute` must go before UseRouting. Therefore I end up with the following sequence:

1. UseStatusCodePagesWithReExecute
2. UseRouting
3. UseRequestLocalization
4. My middleware

The problem now is that my status code error page won't work. If I move my middleware to execute before UseStatusCodePagesWithReExecute then the error page works but the wrong culture is set as I need it placed after UseRequestLocalization.

I'd appreciate it if somone could help as I'm going around in circles trying to fix this.

